description_en: A Type 56 Chicom chest rig. The Type 56 chest rig was made for use with the Chinese Type 56 assault rifle, which was a near direct copy of the Russian AK47. The rig has 7 pouches, 3 for magazines and 4 for grenades along with adjustable shoulder straps and a tied waist cord.

name_en: Soviet Russian SVD Dragunov Magazine Pouch
description_en: A scarce Soviet Russian SVD Dragunov magazine pouch. The heavy canvas pouch holds four 7.62 x 54mm round magazines and a larger inside pocket for the PSO-1 rifle scope and cleaning tools.

name_en: WW2 Imperial Japanese Army Officers Mess Tin
description_en: A WW2 Japanese Army Officers ‘Hango’ or mess / rice cooker set. The aluminium set comprises of the main mess tin, small tray insert and lid. This is a later war example without the metal carry handle.
A very good example of a Russian Army VSR 93 winter coat. The VSR 93 camouflage pattern was first introduced in 1991 to units such as the VDV and by 1994 was issued universally.

A Soviet Afghan war Russian soldiers plastic canteen. The tropical plastic canteen / water bottles were introduced in the early 1980’s as the Afghan war showed the need for larger size water bottles for its soldiers in the harsh hot environment.
